Runbook orders-db ORDDB-002 step 3: Add missing index without locking
command: kubectl exec -it orders-db-primary-0 -- psql -U postgres -c "CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY IF NOT EXISTS idx_orders_<name> ON orders(<columns>);"
note: Always use CONCURRENTLY in production. This takes longer but doesn't lock the table. Monitor progress: SELECT phase, blocks_done, blocks_total FROM pg_stat_progress_create_index;

Runbook redis REDIS-001 step 5: Check for keys without TTL (potential leak)
command: kubectl exec -it redis-0 -- redis-cli --scan --pattern 'session:*' | head -20 | xargs -I{} redis-cli TTL {}
note: TTL of -1 means no expiry — these keys accumulate forever. This is likely a bug in auth-service. Keys should have expiry matching JWT lifetime. Report to identity team.
